        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 8:58AM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 857 AM EDT, Doppler radar indicated thunderstorms near
Blissfield, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Pea to half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Ottawa Lake around 925 AM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Jasper, Rome Center,
Ogden Center, Riga, Palmyra, Fairfield, and Holloway.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
